      <review>
         <snippet>A grand story of redemption, laced with barbecued wit and slopped with intrigue, Chrystal is a high heaping of brilliant storytelling.</snippet>
         <url>http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr/reviews/review_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=2075191</url>
         <critic>Duane Byrge</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>One of those movies that sticks to your mind like a briar to wool slacks. It has no revelations, no high drama, no heartbreaking tragedy. What it does have is bone-deep honesty, and that's enough for once.</snippet>
         <url>http://ae.charlotte.com/entertainment/ui/charlotte/movie.html?id=295871&amp;reviewId=17818</url>
         <critic>Lawrence Toppman</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>Chrystal unravels a bit toward the end as it becomes more fable-like, but the performances make it worthwhile.</snippet>
